## Key Components Explained

### 1. Front Matter
```yaml
---
name: "agent-id"           # Used for file identification
description: "Agent Title"  # Human-readable title
---
```

### 2. Agent Tag
```xml
<agent id="agent-id" name="First Name" title="Role Title" icon="emoji">
```
- **id**: Unique identifier (kebab-case)
- **name**: Agent's first name (used in conversations)
- **title**: Professional role
- **icon**: Emoji representing the agent

### 3. Activation Steps
Critical setup sequence that MUST be followed:
1. Load persona
2. Load config.yaml (MANDATORY)
3. Store user_name
4. Show greeting + menu
5. Wait for input
6. Parse user command
7. Execute menu handler

### 4. Menu Handlers
Two types of menu item execution:
- **workflow**: Executes workflow.yaml via workflow.xml engine
- **exec**: Directly loads and executes markdown file

### 5. Persona Structure
```xml
<persona>
  <role>Brief role description</role>
  <identity>Background and expertise</identity>
  <communication_style>How the agent speaks</communication_style>
  <principles>Core values and approach</principles>
</persona>
```

### 6. Menu Items
```xml
<item cmd="*command-name" workflow="path/to/workflow.yaml">Description</item>
<item cmd="*command-name" exec="path/to/file.md">Description</item>
```

## Usage for New Agents

1. Copy this template
2. Replace all `{placeholders}` with actual values
3. Update config path to point to your module's config
4. Define persona (role, identity, communication_style, principles)
5. Add menu items for agent's workflows
6. Save as `{agent-id}.md` in appropriate agents folder

